A further argument in favour of 12 months: The paintings done for Jonghelinck executed with meticulous care & finish. Tower of Babel, Procession. In the Months Bruegel did not have enough time. The 2nd picture: Hunters in the snow, Dark Day, Hay Making done with great care - Corn Harvest, Return of the Herd in parts only laid on, without complete finish - this would indicated that Jonghelinck wanted them at a certain date, but the great number of paintings to be executed forced this manner of working by Bruegel.

column4: <content>A further argument in favour of 12 months: The paintings done for Jonghelinck executed with meticulous care & finish. Tower of Babel, Procession. In the Months Bruegel did not have enough time. The 2nd picture: Hunters in the snow, Dark Day, Hay Making done with great care - Corn Harvest, Return of the Herd in parts only laid on, without complete finish - this would indicated that Jonghelinck wanted them at a certain date, but the great number of paintings to be executed forced this manner of working by Bruegel.</content>
